<p>
  In this section, we will revist one of the most important questions
  we considered during kinematics: an object falling.
  We will add some new vocabulary and slight changes
  that will aid us in our student of projectile motion.
</p>


<p class = 'definition'>
  An object is in <strong>free-fall</strong>
  it is accelerating at 9.8 m/s<sup>2</sup> downward,
  and the only force acting on that object is gravity.
</p>

