<p>
  Typically, upward is considered the positive direction
  and downward is considered the negative direction.
  For this reason, when an object is falling, almost all
  of our variables will be <emph>negative</emph>.
  (You are allowed to change this for yoru convience,
  but in this section we are trying to get used to the conventional system,
  so please consider the downward direction to be neagative!)
</p>

<p>
  When an object is falling, it is accelerating
  at a constant rate of 9.8 m/s<sup>2</sup> downward.
  So, we are able to use the four <strong>kinematic equations</strong>.
</p>

